            <p>WM. FLEGENHEIMER&#44;<lb/>
                ATTORNEY AND COUNSELLOR AT LAW&#44;<lb/>
                No. 1001 Main St.&#44; cor. 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.<lb/>
                P. O. Box 69.<lb/></p>
            <p>Richmond&#44; Va.&#44; Dec 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1878<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev&#58; S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa<lb/>
                Reverend Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>As officiating Minister of your Congregation you<lb/> conducted the funeral services in the month of<lb/> December 1863 of the late Adelheid Proskauer&#44; the<lb/> wife of J Proskauer of this City&#44; formerly a member of<lb/> your Congregation.  It is of considerable importance<lb/> to Mr J Proskauer to obtain a Certificate of the death<lb/> of his late wife Adelheid&#44; whose maiden name was Block&#44; of<lb/> Breslau&#8212;as there is a small legacy coming to his children<lb/> by that marriage.  He knows of no one to call upon<lb/> for such a Certificate but you.  Will you have the<lb/> kindness to furnish him with a duly attested and<lb/> authenticated certificate&#44; and have the same countersigned<lb/> by the <sic>german</sic> Consul in your city.  You can<lb/> either send me your bill including consular fee<lb/> and I will remit amount to you&#44; or you can<lb/> send the certificate with your bill to Mr<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>J Proskauer West Clay st corner Henry. C.O.D.<lb/> per Express.<lb/>
                Please favor the old gentleman<lb/> at your earliest convenience<lb/>
                and oblige<lb/>
                Yours Very Resp&#39;y<lb/>
                Wm Flegenheimer<lb/></p>
            <p>Please answer<lb/></p>
        </body>
